This paper deals with image compression and classification, which are core topics in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of wavelet transforms, which are commonly used in signal processing and multimedia (cs.MM). The authors propose a method for directly using compressed images in deep learning models, which involves information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of augmentation techniques to improve classification accuracy, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
